article.description: Radford holds off Longwood's second-half rally, 80-75
article.headline: Radford holds off Longwood's second-half rally, 80-75
article.linkText: Radford holds off Longwood's second-half rally, 80-75
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Cameron Jones scored 15 points to lead five Radford players in double figures as the Highlanders beat in-state rival Longwood 80-75 on Wednesday. Quincy Taylor hit back-to-back 3-pointers to cut Longwood's deficit to 75-73 with 22 seconds left. Jalen Carethers answered with a dunk, then Taylor missed a 3 and Radford made 3 of 4 free throws to seal it. Radford (18-8, 9-4) moved into a four-way tie for first place atop the Big South Conference standings. Rashun Davis had 13 points, Ya Ya Anderson 12, and R.J. Price and Brandon Holcomb added 11 apiece for the Highlanders. Radford took a 44-33 lead into the intermission after shooting 58.6 percent, including 8 of 15 3-pointers. Shaquille Johnson led Longwood (7-19, 3-10) with 22 points. Taylor added 16 and Leron Fisher 15. The Lancers opened the second half on a 10-2 run to pull within 46-43. Longwood beat Radford in double overtime on Jan. 3.
